## 🛡️ 3. Tier 3: The Dedicated Backup Target (Proxmox Backup Server)

Your Supermicro 2U chassis functions as your ultimate recovery vault, running Proxmox Backup Server (PBS) directly on bare metal across your 12x 4TB IronWolf CMR array.

### Step A: Datastore Initialization

1. Complete the standard bare-metal installation of Proxmox Backup Server on the Supermicro node.
2. Log into the PBS Web console interface at `https://<SUPERMICRO_IP>:8007`.
3. Navigate to **Administration** -> **Storage/Disks**. Format and group your 12x 4TB IronWolf drives into a large, secure storage space (ZFS Mirror or RAIDZ2 pool).
4. Click **Datastore** -> **Create Datastore** and point the path tracking directly to your mounted IronWolf storage mount point.

### Step B: Syncing Compute to the Vault

1. Inside the PBS Web console, click **Dashboard** and copy the **Fingerprint** security string token.
2. Open your production virtual computing environment host (Dell R710). Go to **Datacenter** -> **Storage** -> **Add Proxmox Backup Server**.
3. Input your Supermicro PBS node IP address, user account configurations (`admin@pbs`), your custom password, and paste the precise security fingerprint string. Click **Add**.

